<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 12 at 4:14PM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...A WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT...
WEATHER...
* Widespread moderate to heavy snow will continue through the
evening.
* Snowfall rates between three-quarter inch to an inch per hour
will be likely within the heavier snow through 6 PM. These
stronger snow rates have led to accumulation on untreated
roadways with temperatures between 32 to 33 degrees.
* East winds around 20 to 25 mph with gusts 35 to 40 mph. Highly
fluctuating visibilities down to a quarter-mile are expected
given the breezy conditions.
IMPACTS...
* Accumulating snow will lead to slippery roads, particularly on
bridges, exit ramps and overpasses.
* Heavy snow will bring a reduction in visibility down to a
quarter-mile.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
